  "summary": "git-userhub postinstall script performs install-time network activity with child_process and host enumeration",
  "details": "On install, this package executes install.js via a postinstall lifecycle hook. install.js loads child_process, makes outbound HTTPS requests (https.get at lines 43 and 78), and references hostname/id-style host-identifying fields. The package name 'git-userhub' has no clear, documented purpose justifying install-time network calls combined with child_process; the shape (lifecycle-hook + outbound network + host identifiers) is consistent with installer-side reconnaissance/exfiltration triggered automatically by 'npm install'.",
